The paper deals with OCR (Optical Character Recognition) on historical documents, which involves natural language processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
